  <thing id="rDraSong" name="Dragon, Song" description="Song dragons are a rare and mysterious race of dragons that prefer life amoung humanity to the company of other dragons.  They can free take on the form of a human woman, and in this guise they live among humankind, revealing their true nature only in times of great personal peril or great crisis.\n\nIn their natural form, song dragons are slim and splendid dragons with iridescent silver-blue scales and the general shape of a copper dragon.  In human form, they appear to be attractive women of 20 to 30 years in age.  They retain full knowledge and awareness regardless of form, and most are consumate actors, so that humans are usually unaware of a song dragon&apos;s identity.\n\n{b}Combat: {/b}\nSong dragons strike quickly and mercilessly with their razor-sharp claws and tend to sing joyously as the fight (although they remain silent if the noise would endanger their allies or the success of their own attack).  In human form, song dragons prefer to use slashing, edged weapons.\n\n{b}In the Realms:{/b}\nFound throughout the Realms, song dragons serve or cooperate with good mages, Harpers (Harper Scouts), and groups and individuals with similar aims or opportunities to preserve, renew, and protect the land.  They are quite common in the Moonshae Isles, a fact that leads mages to speculate that they originated in that land.  They remain shrouded in mystery, however--so much that two accidental sightings of song dragons assuming their natural from once started a panicked rumor that evil wizard were transforming their foes into dragons.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Monsters of Faerun" compset="Race" summary="Song Dragons are rare, beautiful dragons of faerun.">
