  <thing id="rPhaerimm" name="Phaerimm" description="Phaerimm are evil magicians who would gladly erase all other beings from existence. The fact that they have not yet done so is probably attributable to the fact that they would lack serviceable slaves to torture for sport if they did.\n\nPhaerimms resemble 10-to-12-foot-tall windsocks underneath an ovoid head.  The head disk contains a huge toothed maw and its surrounded by four clawed arms.  Beneath their top disk, their long, slnuous bodies taper down to a leathal stinger.  They are powerful magicians, gaining levels sorcerers over lives that span centuries.  Many elder phaerimms are 15th-to 20th level sorcerers; some have even pursued advanced magical study, much like that of human archmages.  Younger phaerims&apos; magical abilities are not so well developed.\n\nIf phaerimms were less evil, they would be more alien and difficult to understand, but their overwehelming drive toward inflicting pain makes them somewhat predictable.  They communicate with one another by varying the wind speed around their bodies.  They communicate with others using telepathy. They understand Common and several other languages.\n\n{b}Combat{/b}\nPhaerimms can be dangerous physical combatants, but they view purely physical combat as a sign of weakness.  Using their stinger or weapons to defend themselves is a sign that their magical abilities are not sufficient.  Consequently, phaerimms only make physical attacks as their last resort, even at low levels when they lack powerful magic.  Low-level phaerimms stoop to using masterwork swords, prefering falchions.\n\nAs spellcasters, phaerimms favor charm, command, and illusion effects over direct damage spells, but they are not shy about letting loose a {i}fireball{/i} if necessary.  Powerful elder phaerimms will often have charmed or otherwise enthralled beings fighting for them.  In fact, phaerimms sometimes pick fights simply to watch their enemies being forced to hack apart their own friends.  Phaerimms also enjoy summoning outsiders, but are generally too proud to use low level summoning spells to call up common animals or other minor creatures.\n\n{b}In the Realms{/b}\nMillennia ago, the phaerims plotted to destroy all life in Faerun.  They succeeded in toppling the mighty Netherese empire and devastating the area now know as the Anauroch Desert, but were foiled by the intervention of the elder sharns.  The sharns imprisoned most of the phaerimms in a magical field beneath the Anauroch.  Only a few phaerimms escaped this imprisonment.  Some of these escapees live in Myth Dranor, squandering their power on internal political squabbles.  Others have conquered the beholder city of Ooltul and are attempting to break through the sharns&apos; barrier to free their fellows.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Monsters of Faerun" compset="Race" summary="Dangerous Faerunian spellcasting abominations.">
