  <thing id="rSharn" name="Sharn" description="Sharns embody magical chaos.  They might rule the world, if they cared, and if they could put their minds to it, but their agenda seems more sophisticated than mere rulership.\n\nSharns have massive 3,000-pound coiling black and silver bodies lit by continual magical flares.  They stand between 12 and 15 feet tall.  A sharn&apos;s three heads and grinning jaws sprout from a single trunk.  No visible eyes, hair or ears mar the smooth black skin above its flairing nostrils.  To move on the ground, it drags its snake like lower body along behind it; sharns fly unless they have a good reason to crawl.  Two massive arm-trunks flare from the sides of its body and another srpouts from itsback.  Each arm-trunk supports three smaller arms equiped with clawed three-digit hands.  Each of the nine small hands has multiple eyes covering it; each of the eyes can see normally and by darkvision.\n\nSharns are a highly magical race.   Some scholars believe they are born of the essence of chaos itself, predating even the dragons.\n\n{b}Sharn Society{/b}\nSharns are not a numerous race.  Sharns society is a bedlam of political argument and social intrigue.  Power struggles, usually based on ideological conflicts, are a constant.  This inward-looking focus does not prevent sharns from becoming embroiled in the affairs of other species, even accross the planes.  Exactly what their agenda is in such cases is almost never obvious.\n\n{b}In the Realms{/b}\nThe sharns fought great wars against the Phaerimms, wars that helped shape Faerun, since the interestection of great sharn magics and great phaerimm magic tended to change the landscape upon which the battlefields were fought, turning mountains into hills and forests into grasslands.  Eventually the sharns compromised on the phaerimm question, imprisoning them under Anauroch until they could figure out what to do with them.   Most of the elder sharns have phased out of existance, leaving young sharns who do not possess the near-omnipotence of the older sharns, and seek to understand their purpose in the world.\n\nThe young sharns may now take a momentary interest in the activities of lesser mortals, but the race still spends the great majority of its time locked in internal debates and experiments.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Monsters of Faerun" compset="Race" summary="Sharn are the embodiment of magic and chaos.">
