  <thing id="rHybsil" name="Hybsil" description="Hybsils are woodland nomads devoted to the dieties of nature, their families and crazy acts of bravery.\n\nThey look like 3-foot-tall centaurs with the bodies of antelopes instead of horses. Coloration of their antelope bodies varies greatly and is wide as their full antelope cousins.  They live in tribes of twenty to eighty individuals and hunt across wide ranges of territory, often quite distant from their camps in order not to lead enemies to their families.  Makes have large forking antlers that molt in the dead of winter and grow back in the spring.  FEmale hybsils have smaller straight or spiral antlers without branches, year round.\n\n{b}Combat{/b}\nBefore attacking, hybsils use their {i}mirror image{/i} ability so that their foes will face three or four leaping, arrow-firing hybsil for every hybsil who is actually present.  Unless they are deliberately attempting to prove their courage, hybsils avoid hand-to-hand combat, prevering to use their mobility to dart in and out of hiding, fire arrows, and retreat.\n\n{b}Hybsils as Characters{/b}\nHybsil characters most often gain levels as druids, rangers, sorcerers and rogues.  Hybsil clerics, which are rare, choose between the domains of Luck, Nature and Trickery.\n\n{b}Hybsil Society{/b}\nUnlike their playful cousins, the pixies, hybsils connot turn invisible, and therefore have more earnest attitudes towards questions of hornor, responsibility, and survival.  The three main virtues of the hybsil society are obligation, vengeance, and daring.  Obligations are weighed by the elders, who keep track of favors owed both within and outside the tribe.  The females who have longer memories than the more impetuous hybsil males, usually call for vengeance. Daring is the prerogative of the young hunters and warriors, both male and female, who count it honorable to dart among enemies, stab them once, and escape. Few hybsils seek the company of nonhybsils.  Some tribes maintain generally positive, though distant relationships with humans, gnomes, and other neighbors.  Other tribes have been betrayed or attacked so often that they count all strangers as foes until proven otherwise.\n\n{b}In the Realms{/b}\nThe Zhents of Zhentil Keep have a long history of paying a bounty of upto 1gp per point on a hybsil antler, as long as its magical efficacy can be assure by virtue of being attached to a hybsil scalp--molted antlers won&apos;t do for the Zhents&apos; alchemists.  Meanwhile, in the Silver Marches, a 14th-level hybsil druid who worships Larue and goes by the name Five Point has become the leader of the second largest druid circle in the northlands.  Five Point has three dire wolverines and an owl as animal companions.  He is notorious for putting a 13 gp bounty on Zhentish scalps.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Monsters of Faerun" compset="Race" summary="Small, centauraform deer fey.">
