  <thing id="rWatGenasi" name="Genasi, Water" description="The endless lapping of wave after wave, the salty sea foam spraying into the air, the bottomless ocean depths with pitiless darkness and breath-stealing pressure&#151;these are the elements of a water genasi&#146;s heart.\n\nWater genasi always display one or more of the following traits: bluegreen skin or hair, blue-black eyes, thin scales covering their bodies, hair that waves and sways as if underwater, a muffled voice resembling the echoing songs of whales, or cold, clammy flesh. They breathe water as easily as air.\n\nTheir personalities vary widely, as they are often raised by members of aquatic races&#151;sahuagin, dolphins, whales, tritons, merfolk, or locathah. They tend to be strongly independent, and believe themselves to be utterly unique individuals.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Monsters of Faerun, Races of Faerun" compset="Race">
